  Licensed under the Mozilla Public License, Version 2.0
  https://libxc.gitlab.io/
  https://github.com/ElectronicStructureLibrary/libxc

The mathematical definitions of exchange-correlation functionals are
from published scientific literature. The variable transformation
conventions (rs, zeta, xt, xs, ts) and input preprocessing logic
(density thresholds, Fermi hole curvature constraint, Cauchy-Schwarz
sigma clamp) follow libxc's implementation in work_{lda,gga,mgga}_inc.c.

Reference:
  S. Lehtola, C. Steigemann, M. J. T. Oliveira, and M. A. L. Marques,
  "Recent developments in libxc -- A comprehensive library of functionals
  for density functional theory", SoftwareX 7, 1-5 (2018).
  https://doi.org/10.1016/j.softx.2017.11.002
